ogue of the Kechris-Louveau-Woodin dichotomy that characterizes when two\ndisjoint sets can be separated by an $F_\\sigma$ set, the determinacy of\nV\\\"a\\\"an\\\"anen's perfect set game for all subsets of ${}^\\kappa\\kappa$, and an\nanalogue of the Jayne-Rogers theorem that characterizes the functions which are\n$\\sigma$-continuous with closed pieces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Jan 2023 20:35:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-01"}
