ormality and uniform convergence\nat dimension free rate $n^{-k^*/(2k^*+1)}$ up till a power of $\\log n$\ndepending on the dimension, where $k^*=k+1$, assuming appropriate\nundersmoothing is used in selecting the $L_1$-norm. We also establish\nasymptotic linearity of plug-in estimators of pathwise differentiable features\nof the target function.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 31 Jan 2023 01:11:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-01"}
